Text:
Unable to accept the fact that Ragnarok was so
easily defeated right before his eyes, Mordred
continues to yell.

Impossible! This is Ragnarok we're talking about...
The most powerful magic entity in recorded history!
How could this...happen?! It's simply not possible!

I will not stand for it! Ragnarok is a living
wonder! A priceless treasure from another dimension!
How pitiful.

If you could only grasp a fraction of Shadow Wisdom,
things wouldn't have ended up like this.

Epsilon and Beta declare with cold expressions as
No. 559 approaches them.
Status report.

The surrounding magical beasts have all been
exterminated.
Well done.
Let's split up the troops as planned.

Monitor the Black Rose and assess the damage in the
surrounding area.

The movements of the rebel forces are of particular
concern.
...Hmph.
(Did she just look at me? Why—)
Nghh!

When Rose turns around, she sees Mordred laughing
emptily, as if his soul had been drained out of
him.

Hah! This must be a dream stemming from my
exhaustion.

It appears I'm stressed out from dealing with these
barbarians!
Otherwise, I would never have such a nightmare!
When Mordred opens his eyes—

He sticks his head into a cross-section of
Ragnarok's severed arm.

Meanwhile, Shadow reflects on the ordeal by himself
in midair.

It was fun like a boss fight in a video game, but
the main character and some of the interesting side
characters were sorta left out...

Plus, it could've at least tied in better with the
main plot...

Shadow turns toward a light shining behind him to
find a mound of flesh from Ragnarok's arm wriggling
about.

The mound of flesh stretches into the sky at
incredible speed appearing right before Shadow.
And what's the deal with reusing special effects...?
Hrraaaaahhh!!!

Letting out a beastly roar, Mordred crawls out of
the mound of flesh appearing as a fusion of man and
Ragnarok.
*sigh*
Typical fail.
